The paper deals with complexity theory and algebraic geometry, which are both central topics in computer science. The paper specifically focuses on the VP vs. VNP conjecture, which is a major open problem in computational complexity theory, and introduces new degenerations of VP and VNP. This suggests that the paper is likely to be classified under cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also uses techniques from algebraic geometry, which suggests that it could be classified under cs.CG (Computational Geometry) and cs.SC (Symbolic Computation). Finally, the paper discusses the problem of separating $\overline{\textrm{VP}}$ from VP, which is related to the study of algebraic varieties and their boundaries, suggesting that the paper could also be classified under cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
